label.value: abnormal temporal bone squamous part morphology

value.value: 側頭鱗骨の形態異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal temporal bone squamous part morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the anterosuperior portion of the temporal bone that is thin, scale-like, and translucent and forms part of the lateral wall of the cranial vault
側頭骨の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the temporal bone, typically resulting in decreased size
耳石器官の異常
any structural anomaly in the utricle and saccule of the inner ear which possess otoliths and respond to linear acceleration and deceleration, including gravity
蝸牛迷路の異常

any structural anomaly in the portion of the membranous labyrinth concerned with the sense of hearing (vs. the vestibular labyrinth, which is concerned with the sense of equilibration) and innervated by the cochlear nerve; it is located within the cochlea of the bony labyrinth, and consists of the cochlear duct, which contains the spiral organ
前庭迷路の異常

any structural anomaly in the portion of the membranous labyrinth concerned with the sense of equilibration (vs. the cochlear labyrinth, which is concerned with the sense of hearing) and innervated by the vestibular nerve; it is located within the semicircular canals and vestibule of the bony labyrinth, and consists of the utricle, saccule, and the semicircular, utriculosaccular, and endolymphatic ducts
Ⅰ型前庭細胞の異常

any structural anomaly in the flask-shaped sensory cells of the maculae and cristae of the vestibular labyrinth of the inner ear, which are normally enclosed in calyx endings of afferent neurons; afferent and efferent nerve fibers of the vestibular nerve synapse with them; from the apical end of each cell a bundle of stereocilia and a kinocilium extend into the otolithic membrane of the maculae or the cupula of the cristae
Ⅱ型前庭細胞の異常

any structural anomaly in the cylindrical sensory cells of the maculae and cristae of the vestibular labyrinth of the inner ear which are normally contacted by bouton endings of afferent and efferent neurons; afferent and efferent nerve fibers of the vestibular nerve synapse with them; from the apical end of each cell a bundle of stereocilia and a kinocilium extend into the otolithic membrane of the maculae or the cupula of the cristae
クラウディウス細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly in the columnar cells located on the floor of the ductus cochlearis external to the spiral organ (also known as the organ of Corti)
有毛細胞機械電気変換の異常
anomalous conversion of mechanical energy into electric(al) energy by sensory cells, such as auditory and vestibular hair cells, required for auditory sensation
蝸牛有毛細胞の生理異常

any functional anomaly in processes pertinent to the integrated function of cochlear hair cells i.e. the sensory cells in the spiral organ which are in synaptic contact with sensory as well as efferent fibers of the cochlear (auditory) nerve

label.value: abnormal cochlear inner hair cell physiology

value.value: 蝸牛内耳有毛細胞の生理異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal cochlear inner hair cell physiology

value.value: any functional anomaly in processes pertinent to the function of cochlear IHCs which constitute the true sensory cell type sending impulses via the cochlear (auditory) nerve

label.value: abnormal cochlear outer hair cell physiology

value.value: 蝸牛外耳有毛細胞の生理異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal cochlear outer hair cell physiology

value.value: any functional anomaly in processes pertinent to the function of cochlear OHCs which are known to enhance the performance of the cochlea, both qualitatively (increased selectivity) and quantitatively (increased sensitivity); in addition to the mechanoelectric transduction required for auditory sensation, OHCs also perform electromechanical transduction, whereby transmembrane voltage drives rapid changes in the length and stiffness of OHCs at audio frequencies in vitro (electromotility)

label.value: abnormal cochlear outer hair cell electromotility

value.value: 蝸牛外耳有毛細胞の電気的運動性異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal cochlear outer hair cell electromotility

value.value: anomalous motility of the cochlear OHCs in response to electrical stimulation; normally, the motile response (i.e. rapid change in length and stiffness of OHCs) is closely coupled to the changing transduction current and provides a region-specific amplification in the movement of the spiral organ that enhances transduction at the IHCs in that specific region of the cochlear spiral, increasing both sensitivity and specificity; electromotility is believed to arise through voltage-gated conformational changes in motor protein (prestin) or proteins located in the lateral wall of the OHC

label.value: absent cochlear outer hair cell electromotility

value.value: 蝸牛外耳有毛細胞の電気的運動性欠損

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: absent cochlear outer hair cell electromotility

value.value: absence or loss of motility of the cochlear OHCs in response to electrical stimulation

label.value: decreased cochlear outer hair cell electromotility

value.value: 蝸牛外耳有毛細胞の電気的運動性減少

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: decreased cochlear outer hair cell electromotility

value.value: reduced motility of the cochlear OHCs in response to electrical stimulation
前庭有毛細胞の生理異常
anomalies in processes pertinent to the integrated function of the sensory epithelium of the maculae and cristae in the membranous labyrinth of the inner ear
メッケル軟骨の欠如

absence of this cartilage bar in the mandibular arch that forms a temporary supporting structure in the embryonic mandible; gives rise to middle ear bones and sphenomandibular and anterior malleolar ligaments
後頭骨の欠如
absence of the bone at the lower, posterior part of the skull
後頭骨の矮小化
reduced size of the bone at the lower, posterior part of the skull
後頭骨孔
presence of a hole in the bone at the lower, posterior part of the skull
上後頭骨の欠如
absence of the bone on the dorsal side of the great foramen of the skull, usually forming a part of the occipital in the adult, but distinct in the young
上後頭骨の矮小化
reduced size of the bone on the dorsal side of the great foramen of the skull, usually forming a part of the occipital in the adult, but distinct in the young
外後頭骨の矮小化
reduced size of the bone or region on the lateral sides of the great foremen of the skull, which often forms a part of the occipital in the adult, but is usually distinct in the young
外後頭骨の開裂

the appearance of an abnormal division in the bone or region on the lateral sides of the great foremen of the skull, which often forms a part of the occipital in the adult, but is usually distinct in the young
後頭骨底部の矮小化
reduced size of the bone in the base of the cranium, frequently forming a part of the occipital in the adult, but usually distinct in the young
前蝶形骨の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the anterior part of the body of the sphenoid bone in front of the basisphenoid; it is usually a separate bone in the young or fetus, but becomes a part of the sphenoid in the adult
前蝶形骨の欠如
absence of the anterior part of the body of the sphenoid bone in front of the basisphenoid; it is usually a separate bone in the young or fetus, but becomes a part of the sphenoid in the adult
前蝶形骨の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the presphenoid bone, typically resulting in decreased size
前蝶形骨の短縮
reduced length of the anterior part of the body of the sphenoid bone in front of the basisphenoid; it is usually a separate bone in the young or fetus, but becomes a part of the sphenoid in the adult
翼状突起の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the process projecting downward from either side of the sphenoid bone, in vertebrates divided into two plates, an inner and an outer (sometimes called the lateral and medial); the posterior nares pass through the space, called the pterygoid fossa, between the processes
翼状骨の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the bone region which corresponds to the inner plate of the pterygoid process of the mammalian skull
翼状突起の欠如

absence of the process projecting downward from either side of the sphenoid bone, in vertebrates divided into two plates, an inner and an outer (sometimes called the lateral and medial); the posterior nares pass through the space, called the pterygoid fossa, between the processes
翼状骨の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the pterygoid bone, typically resulting in decreased size
翼状骨の矮小化
reduced size of the bone region which corresponds to the inner plate of the pterygoid process of the mammalian skull
眼窩蝶形骨の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the bone that is situated in the orbit on either side of the presphenoid; it generally forms a part of the sphenoid in the adult, and may be independent in the young
蝶形骨大翼の欠損
absence of the broad curved wing like expanses on each side of the sphenoid bone in adults; may exist independently in the young
蝶形骨大翼の矮小化
reduced size of either of the broad curved wing like expanses on each side of the sphenoid bone in adults; may exist independently in the young
蝶形骨大翼の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the alisphenoid bone, typically resulting in decreased size
底蝶形骨の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the basisphenoid bone, typically resulting in decreased size
底蝶形骨の矮小化

reduced size of part of the base of the cranium between the basioccipital and the presphenoid, which usually ossifies separately in the embryo or in the young, and becomes a part of the sphenoid in the adult; in many animals it persists as a separate bone between the basioccipital bone and the presphenoidal bone
底蝶形骨孔

the presence of one or more holes in part of the base of the cranium between the basioccipital and the presphenoid, which usually ossifies separately in the embryo or in the young, and becomes a part of the sphenoid in the adult; in many animals it persists as a separate bone between the basioccipital bone and the presphenoidal bone

label.value: absent strial basal cell tight junctions

value.value: 基底線条細胞のタイトジャンクションの欠如

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: absent strial basal cell tight junctions

value.value: absence of tight junctions from the basal cell layer of stria vascularis, resulting in destruction of the paracellular barrier between basal cells; loss of basal cell tight junctions renders the intrastrial space open to perilymph and abolishes its electrical isolation

label.value: degeneration of organ of Corti supporting cells

value.value: コルチ器支持細胞の縮退

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: degeneration of organ of Corti supporting cells

value.value: degeneration or loss of the highly differentiated epithelial cells with distinctive morphological features that surround all hair cells in the organ of Corti
蝸牛外耳有毛細胞の短縮
reduced height of the sensory cells of the organ of Corti which are in synaptic contact with sensory as well as efferent fibers of the auditory nerve
頬骨の欠如
absence of the quadrilateral bone that forms the prominence of the cheek
頬骨の矮小化
reduced size of the quadrilateral bone that forms the prominence of the cheek
頬骨弓の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the bony arch in vertebrates that extends along the side or front of the skull beneath the eye socket and is formed by the temporal process of the zygomatic bone and the zygomatic process of the temporal bone
鼻骨の矮小化
reduced size of either of two rectangular bone plates forming the bridge of the nose
鼻骨の短縮
reduced length of either of two rectangular bone plates forming the bridge of the nose
鼻骨幅の拡大
increased width of either of two rectangular bone plates forming the bridge of the nose
